article.headline: Texas-Pan American 72, W. Illinois 59
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. (AP) -- Senior Paul Stoll scored 22 points to lead Texas-Pan American to a 72-59 victory over Western Illinois Wednesday night. Nathan Hawkins added 17 points and Brian Burrell chipped in 11 points and nine rebounds for the Broncs (4-2). Stoll had eight assists and five 3-pointers for Texas Pan-American, which led 26-23 at the half. David Jackson scored a game-high 28 points on 13-for-17 shooting for the Leathernecks (2-4). David DuBois had 14 points and eight rebounds for Western Illinois. Texas-Pan American shot 24-for-52 from the field, or 46.2 percent, compared with Western Illinois' 23-for-60, or 38.3 percent.
